# TSDoc (protocol)

## Classes

Add a **`/** ... */`** block on every **exported class**: short **summary**; add **`@remarks`** or **`@example`** when behavior or usage is non-obvious.

## Public methods

Document every **public** method: **summary**, **`@param`** per parameter, **`@returns`**, and **`@throws`** when callers must handle errors.

## Example

```typescript
/**
 * Handles intent lifecycle and persistence.
 * @remarks Delegates to adapters for DB and queue; does not call other services.
 */
export class IntentService {
  /**
   * Creates an intent and enqueues indexing jobs.
   * @param input - Validated intent payload
   * @returns The created intent with id
   */
  async create(input: CreateIntentInput): Promise<Intent> {
    // ...
  }
}
```

Private helpers: document only when the logic is subtle or cross-cutting.
